        "timestamp": "2021-01-15 09:59:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> would it not make sense -even it is not connected -  to use the integration python baseline image? (alpine based)\n\nHere I'm replacing VM image. I'm open to work on creating VM image similar to integration python baseline Docker image.\n\nJust to clarify: main purpose of this Vagrant environment is to be able to demo changes made on internal laboratory infrastructure without requiring direct access to it. I believe it might be beneficial to keep Integration base images consistent for both Docker containers and VMs but I thought any VM image with Python would do for demo purposes.\n\nLet me know what you think",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
